commands.welcome_message:
"Welcome to the RLBot Discord server!  Whether you want to make bots in Rocket League, watch other people make bots, or lend a hand any other way this is the place for you!

Some rules:
- The framework CANNOT be used online.  Do not ask how to use it online.  You can be banned without warning if you clearly have malicious intent (crate farming, etc.).  We want to stay on Psyonix's good side here.
- Don't do other mean things that can get you banned.  Harassment, vulgarity, spamming, and other obvious offensive things.
- Try to find the appropriate channel for discussion when sending messages.

Getting started:
- Visit the website for language-specific instructions: <http://www.rlbot.org/>
- How to set up a bot for Python: <https://youtu.be/UjsQFNN0nSA>
- Text tutorial series: <https://www.reddit.com/r/RocketLeagueBots/wiki/botguidepart1>
- Video tutorial series: <https://youtu.be/NjJzPoo16iQ>
- Check the #faq channel
- Ask for help in #issues-and-bugs

Links:
- Website (to see supported languages and info): <http://www.rlbot.org/>
- League and bot info: <https://braacket.com/league/rlbot>
- Twitch channel: <https://www.twitch.tv/rlbotofficial>

Please go to the appropriate channel to post:
<#265940354451111936> - Anything related to RLBot, and for welcoming new people
#bot-clips - For posting clips of your bots
#issues-and-bugs - For any issues you're having, and bug reports for RLBot
#strategy-discussion - For discussing tactics, code, and bot strategy
#ml-discussion - For discussing machine learning or ML Rocket League bots
#tournament - For any discussion about bot competitions
#off-topic - No topic because it's off-topic
#solo-queue-cure - For any "Looking for Game" or just to talk about your experiences in multiplayer
#learn-programming - For people learning programming languages
#framework-dev - Contributing to tools and frameworks that help all bot makers"
